{"id":"334726649_From_Stress_Chains_to_Acoustic_Emission","abstract":"A numerical scheme using the combined finite-discrete element method is employed to study a model of an earthquake system comprising a granular layer embedded in a formation. When the formation is driven so as to shear the granular layer, a system of stress chains emerges. The stress chains endow the layer with resistance to shear and on failure launch broadcasts into the formation. These broadcasts, received as acoustic emission, provide a remote monitor of the state of the granular layer of the earthquake system.","authors":["Ke Gao","Robert Guyer","Esteban Rougier","Christopher Ren"],"meta":["July 2019Physical Review Letters 123(4):048003","DOI:10.1103/PhysRevLett.123.048003"],"references":["329715891_Continuous_chatter_of_the_Cascadia_subduction_zone_revealed_by_machine_learning","324218776_Modeling_of_Stick-Slip_Behavior_in_Sheared_Granular_Fault_Gouge_Using_the_Combined_Finite-Discrete_Element_Method","313858017_Machine_Learning_Predicts_Laboratory_Earthquakes","264386901_A_framework_for_grand_scale_parallelization_of_the_combined_finite_discrete_element_method_in_2D","238559524_Force_chains_seismogenic_faults_visualized_with_photoelastic_granular_shear_experiments","230948520_Statistics_of_slipping_event_sizes_in_granular_seismic_fault_models","216831943_The_Mechanics_of_Earthquake_Faulting","8137184_Nonvolcanic_Tremors_Deep_Beneath_the_San_Andreas_Fault","7388785_Characterization_of_force_chains_in_granular_material","325373011_Sounds_of_Failure_Passive_Acoustic_Measurements_of_Excited_Vibrational_Modes","319346443_Influence_of_Weakening_Minerals_on_Ensemble_Strength_and_Slip_Stability_of_Faults","318181568_On_the_micromechanics_of_slip_events_in_sheared_fluid-saturated_fault_gouge_Stick-Slip_Dynamics_in_Saturated_Gouge","316216511_The_combined_finite-discrete_element_method","305339921_Connecting_slow_earthquakes_to_huge_earthquakes","285758076_Stick-slip_behavior_in_a_continuum-granular_